# Per-instance render state inventory: `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive`

Scope: one skeletal appearance template (e.g. `appearance/jawa_m.sat`) instantiated N times in one scene, standard (non-batch) path unless noted. File:line references are to this repo.

---

## Frame pipeline (context)

Within one camera cell:

1. **Traversal / add pass** — `ObjectList::render()` sets each appearance’s world transform, then `SkeletalAppearance2::render()` selects LOD, sets skinning mode, and calls `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::add()` (which calls `prepareToView()` and captures sort keys). Batch-eligible appearances call `FullGeometrySkeletalAppearanceBatchRenderer::submit()` instead, which calls `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` during this pass.

2. **Draw pass** — `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::popCell()` sorts, then for each entry calls `prepareToDraw()` then `draw()` back-to-back (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:725–781`).

---

## State inventory table

| State | Owner + file:line | Lifetime | Shared or per-instance | How instances can diverge at draw time |
|-------|-------------------|----------|------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| **Appearance world transform** (`m_appearanceToWorld`) | `Appearance` — `Appearance.h:202`, set via `Appearance.cpp:448`, read `Appearance.h:237–239` | Set each frame in `ObjectList::render()` before render (`ObjectList.cpp:312`); lives for appearance lifetime | **Per appearance instance** | Different object `Transform_o2w` per Jawa |
| **Display LOD index** (`m_displayLodIndex`) | `SkeletalAppearance2` — selected in `SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1631`, vector accessed `SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:800–803` | Recomputed every `render()` from screen size (`calculateDisplayLodIndex`, `SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:3888+`); restored in UI context | **Per appearance instance** | Distance, LOD bias, `CharacterLodManager`, `m_userControlledDetailLevel`, global max-LOD cap |
| **Primitive LOD index** (`m_lodIndex`, const) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:133` | Fixed at construction (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:389`); primitive lives until LOD shader-prim vector cleared/rebuilt (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:4414–4417`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** (one primitive set per LOD) | Only the vector for `m_displayLodIndex` is used at render; instances at different display LODs use different primitive sets / mesh topologies |
| **Skeleton / joint transforms** (`m_jointToRootTransforms`) | `Skeleton` — `Skeleton.cpp:1338–1493` | Lazily computed once per skeleton per frame (`m_frameLastJointToRootCalculate`, `Skeleton.cpp:1345–1349`); backing store rebuilt on skeleton modification (`Skeleton.cpp:1875+`) | **Per appearance × LOD skeleton** | Animation resolver state, active animations, transform modifiers, `m_overridingAnimationResolver` copy (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1527–1533`) |
| **Bone matrix array for skinning** (`m_bindPoseModelToRootTransforms`, `PoseModelTransform[]`) | `Skeleton` — `Skeleton.cpp:1498–1550`, accessed `Skeleton.cpp:1696–1709` | Lazily computed once per skeleton per frame (`m_frameLastBindPoseModelToRootCalculate`); array (re)allocated in `Skeleton.cpp:1893–1895` | **Per appearance × LOD skeleton** | Derived from joint transforms + per-segment bind-pose model→joint data; diverges with animation/pose |
| **Animation resolver rotation/translation caches** (`m_rotations`, `m_translations`, `m_transformEvaluatedFlags`) | `TransformAnimationResolver` — `TransformAnimationResolver.cpp:668–705`, reset `TransformAnimationResolver.cpp:790–800` | Evaluated lazily per transform index; flags cleared every `alter()` | **Per appearance instance** | Different animation tracks, wearables, action state |
| **Skinning source mesh data** (`m_sourceVectors`, `m_transformData`, `m_sourceDot3Vectors`, `m_sourceData`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:147–150`, filled `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1315–1382` | Created in `_initialize()` at primitive construction; freed in destructor (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:431`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** (same template topology if same LOD/mesh) | Rebuilt mesh/wearables change weights/topology per instance after `rebuildMesh()` |
| **Skinning mode** (`m_skinningMode`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:155`, set `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1136–1138` | Set each frame in `SkeletalAppearance2::render()` before add/submit (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1768–1769`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Screen fraction thresholds (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1737–1742`), `mustUseSoftSkinning`, `m_forceHardSkinningEnabled` |
| **Every-other-frame skinning flag** (`m_everyOtherFrameSkinningEnabled`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:161`, logic `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1717–1731` | Set each render from appearance (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1770`) | **Per appearance** (applied to all its primitives) | Owner network ID parity vs frame number |
| **Skinned-this-frame flag** (`m_hasBeenSkinned`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:156`, set `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1824` | Mutable across frames; gates skip paths in `skinData()` (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1739–1741`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Prior skinning this frame (e.g. batch submit then collide) changes whether `SM_noSkinning` skips rewrite |
| **System vertex buffer** (`m_systemStream`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:139`, created `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1399–1409` | Allocated at primitive init; CPU `byte[]` (`SystemVertexBuffer.h:86`); skinned every `prepareToDraw()` / `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Skinned positions/normals/dot3 differ with pose; constant UV/color slots filled once at init (`fillConstantVertexBufferData`, `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1646–1707`) unless rebuild |
| **Dynamic vertex buffer object** (`m_dynamicStream`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:137`, created `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1274` | One `DynamicVertexBuffer` per primitive for life of primitive; **not** preserved across locks (`DynamicVertexBuffer.h:178–180`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** (object); **ring backing store shared** at D3D11 plugin level (`Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:268–272`) | Per-lock slice content differs with pose; ring slot chosen at lock time |
| **Dynamic VB bound offset** (`m_offset` on graphics data) | `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData` — `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.h:113`, set `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:331`, consumed `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:2267–2280` | Set on each `lock()`; read when `Graphics::setVertexBuffer(*m_dynamicStream)` runs in `prepareToDraw()` (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:819`) | **Per lock / per primitive** (stored on that DVB’s graphics data); ring is **shared** | Ring allocator position at lock time; `forceDiscard` / ring wrap (`Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:302–314`) |
| **Dynamic VB sort key** (`m_sortKey`) | `DynamicVertexBuffer` — `DynamicVertexBuffer.h:108`, from `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData::getSortKey()` `Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:495–497` | Set at DVB construction (`DynamicVertexBuffer.cpp:84`); **not** updated on lock | **Shared key** for all skin-format DVBs (ring buffer pointer) | Does not encode slice offset; affects sort grouping only |
| **Static constant vertex buffer** (`m_staticStream`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:138`, created multi-stream only `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1392–1396` | Built once at init; static for primitive lifetime | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Only if `ms_useMultiStreamVertexBuffers`; runtime comment says this is off (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:567–568`) |
| **Vertex buffer bind set** (`m_vertexBufferVector`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:140`, created `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1401` or `1416` | Created at init; points at `m_dynamicStream` (single-stream) or `m_staticStream`+`m_dynamicStream` (multi-stream) | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Which streams are bound at draw |
| **Index buffer** (`m_indexBuffer`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:142`, built `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1466–1636` | Created at init; static contents unless primitive rebuilt | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Rebuild after wearable/mesh changes; topology identical for same LOD/template |
| **Render commands** (`m_renderCommands`, `RenderCommand` fields) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:135`, `RenderCommand` `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:294–314` | Built at init; `draw()` iterates (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:828–832`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** | Static after build; `m_minimumVertexBufferIndex`, `m_startIndexBufferIndex`, cull flip |
| **Shader instance** (`m_shader`) | `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.h:124`, fetched `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:1177` | `fetchModifiableShader()` at init; released in dtor (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:428–429`) | **Per shader-primitive instance** (modifiable copy) | Customization data, texture renderers, shader `alter()` state |
| **StaticShader snapshot for draw** | `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::Phase::Entry` — captured at `add()` via `prepareToView()` `ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:1159`, used `ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:705–746` | Captured during traversal; used at popCell draw | **Per queued draw entry** | Textures/uniforms resolved at add-time `prepareToView`; customization baked into that shader instance |
| **Graphics object-to-world** (global) | Set `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:490–491` from `m_appearance.getTransform_w()` | Set in each primitive’s `prepareToDraw()`; consumed in that primitive’s `draw()` | **Global Graphics state**, overwritten per primitive | Each Jawa’s `m_appearanceToWorld` |
