---

## Lazily-built / cached resources and rebuild triggers

| Resource | Built when | Rebuilt when | Freed when |
|----------|------------|--------------|------------|
| Shader primitives (whole SBSSP) | `SkeletalMeshGeneratorTemplate.cpp:3445` during `rebuildMesh()` | `rebuildMesh(lodIndex)` on dirty LOD, wearable changes, async load completion (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:2155+`) | `unloadUnusedResources()` after `freeShaderPrimFrameCount` idle frames (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:4350–4417`); destructor |
| `m_indexBuffer`, `m_renderCommands` | `_initialize()` / `buildIndexBufferAndRenderCommands()` | Only with new primitive | Primitive destructor |
| `m_staticStream` constant UVs/colors | `_initialize()` `fillConstantVertexBufferData()` | Only with new primitive | Primitive destructor |
| `m_sourceVectors` / weight tables | `_initialize()` | Only with new primitive | Primitive destructor |
| Skeleton joint / bind-pose arrays | First access each frame | Frame counter mismatch (`Os::getNumberOfUpdates()`) | Skeleton modification / resize |
| Animation transform components | First `getTransformComponents()` per index per frame | Every `TransformAnimationResolver::alter()` clears flags | Resolver lifetime |
| `m_systemStream` skinned positions | Every `prepareToDraw()` or `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` | Every skin call (subject to skip flags) | Primitive lifetime |
| `m_dynamicStream` GPU slice | Every `prepareToDraw()` lock/copy | Every frame drawn (not preserved across locks) | Primitive lifetime; ring slots recycled |
| `m_representativeColor` | First `getRepresentativeColor()` | When `m_haveRepresentativeColor` false | Primitive lifetime |
| Display LOD primitive vector | Per-LOD vectors in `m_perLodShaderPrimitives` | LOD switch selects different pre-built vector; rebuild per LOD when dirty | `unloadUnusedResources` per LOD |

---

## Deferred producer → consumer gaps (same frame)

Items written in an earlier pass and consumed in a later pass within one frame, and what (if anything) keeps the produced value intact.

| Producer → Consumer | Producer pass / location | Consumer pass / location | Survival guarantee |
|---------------------|------------------------|--------------------------|-------------------|
| **`prepareToView()` / StaticShader + textures** | Object traversal: `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::add()` (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:1159`) | `popCell` draw: `Graphics::setStaticShader(staticShader, pass)` (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:746`) | `Entry.staticShader` pointer held in sorter queue until draw; shader instance is per-primitive `m_shader`. No re-call to `prepareToView` at draw time. |
| **Sort keys** (incl. `getVertexBufferSortKey()` → DVB ring pointer) | At `add()` (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:405`, `497`) | Sort at `popCell` (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:858`) | Stored in `Entry` at add time. Sort key does **not** include dynamic slice offset. |
| **`m_skinningMode` / every-other-frame flag** | `SkeletalAppearance2::render()` before add (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1768–1770`) | `prepareToDraw()` / `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` at popCell or batch draw | Per-primitive fields on live object; no explicit fence—assumes no other code resets them between render traversal and popCell on main thread. |
| **Bone matrices** (`getBindPoseModelToRootTransforms`) | First skinning touch during traversal (batch `getSkinnedVertexBuffer`) or `prepareToDraw` | Draw-time skinning or batch copy | Per-skeleton frame cache (`m_frameLastBindPoseModelToRootCalculate`). **Invalidated next frame** by `alter()`, not mid-frame. Mid-frame risk if same skeleton skinned, then animation override applied, then skinned again—unusual path. |
| **`m_systemStream` skinned CPU vertices (batch path)** | Render traversal: `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` in `submit()` (`FullGeometrySkeletalAppearanceBatchRenderer.cpp:467–468`, `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:923–936`) | `popCell`: `renderBuffers()` reads `sourceVb` (`FullGeometrySkeletalAppearanceBatchRenderer.cpp:225–235`) | **Per-instance CPU buffer** persists in `m_systemStream` until next skin call on that primitive. **No lock/fence** against `collide()` / second `getSkinnedVertexBuffer()` on same primitive before batch draw (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:988–1006` documents this hazard). |
| **`m_dynamicStream` ring slice (standard path)** | `prepareToDraw()` lock → skin/copy → unlock (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:754–781`) | Same entry’s `draw()` immediately after (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:725–781`) | Sorter calls `prepareToDraw` then `draw` back-to-back per entry. **Offset** stored on that DVB’s graphics data at lock; bound in same `prepareToDraw`. Shared skin ring (`Direct3d11_DynamicVertexBufferData.cpp:268–272`): later primitives’ locks append slices; earlier slice remains mapped until ring discard. Sequential per-entry draw limits overwrite-before-draw for earlier entries. |
| **Graphics global VB bind + `m_offset`** | `prepareToDraw()` → `Graphics::setVertexBuffer` (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:819`) | Same entry’s `draw()` → `RenderCommand::render` (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:306–314`) | Global state; next primitive’s `prepareToDraw` overwrites. Safe only because consumer draw is immediate. |
| **Graphics global object-to-world** | `prepareToDraw()` (`SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:490–491`) | Same entry’s shader passes / draw | Same immediate pairing; overwritten by next primitive. |
| **Batch combined dynamic VB** | `LocalShaderPrimitive::draw()` → `renderBuffers()` lock/copy (`FullGeometrySkeletalAppearanceBatchRenderer.cpp:193–285`) | Same function → `Graphics::drawIndexedTriangleList()` (`290`) | Lock, fill, unlock, bind, draw in one call stack; no deferral beyond function body. |
| **Animation resolver evaluations** | Lazy during first skeleton eval in frame | Any later skin/collide in same frame | `m_transformEvaluatedFlags` per index; cleared only on next `alter()`. Stale mid-frame if `copyTransformsFrom` after eval (`SkeletalAppearance2.cpp:1527–1533`)—edge case. |

### Not a same-frame deferred gap (notable)

- **Standard-path `prepareToDraw` → `draw`**: Same sorter loop iteration (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:725–781`); not a cross-pass deferral for a given primitive.
- **`m_indexBuffer` / `m_renderCommands`**: Produced at construction; consumed every draw without intermediate rewrite.
- **`m_staticStream` / constant UVs in `m_systemStream`**: Written at init; not per-frame producers in the draw path.

---

## Shared vs per-instance summary (multiple identical `jawa_m.sat`)

**Shared (template / global):** mesh construction template data, skeleton templates, shader templates, D3D11 skin ring buffer backing store, batch renderer singleton buffers, `ms_useMultiStreamVertexBuffers`, global Graphics API state slots.

**Per instance (can differ at draw):** `m_appearanceToWorld`, animation resolver + skeleton pose arrays, `m_displayLodIndex` selection, per-primitive `m_shader` + customization, each SBSSP’s `m_dynamicStream`/`m_systemStream`/`m_indexBuffer`/source weights, skinning mode flags, fade state, batch-submitted skinned CPU buffer contents, dynamic VB slice contents and bound offset for that draw.

This maps the code paths faithfully; it does not assert which of the deferred gaps is responsible for any observed rendering defect.
